# Model Selection Rules for ITAMS Project

## Primary: Ollama Cloud (Kimi K2.7 Code) ☁️
**Use when:**
- Reading project structure or multiple files (>3 files)
- Architecture/design questions
- Analyzing complex logic (workflow, email, exchange rate)
- Refactoring large modules
- Context size > 50K tokens
- Need 256K context window

**Avoid when:**
- Credits < 20% remaining (check via PowerShell script)
- Network is slow/unstable
- Simple single-line edits

## Secondary: Ollama Local (Qwen 2.5 Coder 3b) 🤖
**Use when:**
- Simple code edits (single file, <100 lines changed)
- Bug fixes with clear description
- Quick Q&A about specific code
- File creation with clear spec
- Context < 50K tokens
- Ollama Cloud unavailable/slow

**Avoid when:**
- Need to understand multiple files at once
- Complex refactoring across modules

## Tertiary: GitHub Copilot Pro ⚡
**Use when:**
- Inline completion while typing
- Quick chat (no tool calls needed)
- Short single-line questions
- No file reading/writing required

**Avoid when:**
- Need to read/edit files
- Complex multi-step tasks

## Automatic Switching Rules

### Switch FROM Ollama Cloud TO Local when:
- 2 consecutive failures/timeouts from Cloud
- Cloud response time > 30 seconds
- User mentions "credits" or "token limit"
- Daily Cloud usage > 80% of plan

### Switch FROM Local TO Cloud when:
- Local model gives wrong/incomplete answer 2+ times
- Need to read >3 files in one task
- Task involves architecture decisions
- User asks "analyze" or "review" large code

### Switch TO Copilot when:
- Task is just inline completion
- User is typing and wants quick suggestion
- No tools needed

## Token Budget Tracking
- Ollama Cloud: ~80% of monthly credits
- Local: unlimited (free)
- Copilot Pro: 300 premium requests/month (check usage)